      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To efficiently solve this problem with the given constraints, we can use an adjacency list representation of the graph. However, instead of storing all edges, we only store the edges that are reachable from each node. This way, we avoid storing all edges and reduce the memory usage.\n\nWe can use a Disjoint Set Union (DSU) data structure to keep track of the connected components. The DSU data structure will store the parent of each node and the rank of each node.\n\nHere is a Python solution that uses the above approach:\n\n```python\nclass DSU:\n    def __init__(self, n):\n        self.parent = list(range(n))\n        self.rank = [0] * n\n\n    def find(self, x):\n        if self.parent[x] != x:\n            self.parent[x] = self.find(self.parent[x])\n        return self.parent[x]\n\n    def union(self, x, y):\n        root_x = self.find(x)\n        root_y = self.find(y)\n        if root_x != root_y:\n            if self.rank[root_x] > self.rank[root_y]:\n                self.parent[root_y] = root_x\n            elif self.rank[root_x] < self.rank[root_y]:\n                self.parent[root_x]",
